Before the first dawn split the dark, when the world was still a breath held too long, the **First Hunger** awoke. It was not a beast, nor a storm—it was the gnawing in the bellies of the **People of the Ash**, the ones who scraped the earth for roots and chewed the hides of dead things. They had no name for it, only the hollow ache that followed them like a shadow. Then came the **First Answer**: a voice in the crackling of the fire, a hand in the dark that pressed a warm stone into a child’s palm. The voice said: *"Give, and you will be given."*

